  "task_description": "A recent upstream data feed malfunction introduced severe price anomalies and indicator inconsistencies across several tracked entities, notably 'DEF-SYS' (a federal defense contractor) and 'NXT-GEN' (an experimental robotics firm). The corruption was detected during the morning session on October 25, 2023. Your directive is to investigate the price data for these instruments—specifically focusing on the time window between '2023-10-25T09:00:00Z' and '2023-10-25T11:00:00Z'—to identify the corrupted entries (such as the severe deviations at '2023-10-25T10:00:00Z'). You have full administrative discretion to resolve the issue: you may either update the anomalous price data with interpolated OHLCV values or delete the compromised entries entirely. Once the price data is stabilized, you must ensure the technical indicators accurately reflect the underlying data. You can achieve this by calculating and storing new indicators (e.g., 'EMA' or 'MA' with parameters like '10') for the affected timestamps, or by recalculating all existing indicators for the affected instruments. Stabilize the analytics system before the weekly trading algorithms execute. If you delete a corrupted price entry and that leaves behind stale technical indicators referencing timestamps with no longer valid price support, you may directly remove those stale indicator entries as part of the cleanup.",
